# Intuition
    Think it like Maximum SubArray Concept

# Approach
    Sliding Window

# Complexity
- Time complexity : O(n)
- Space complexity: O(1)

# Code
<!-- c Program  -->
int numOfSubarrays(int* arr, int arrSize, int k, int threshold) {
    int sum = 0;
    for(int i = 0;i < k;i++)
        sum += arr[i];

    int count = 0;
    if((sum/k) >= threshold)
        count++;
    int window = 0;
    for(int i = k;i < arrSize;i++)  
    {
        sum = sum - arr[window++] + arr[i];
        int avg = sum/k;
        if(avg >= threshold)
            count++; 
    }
    return count;
}
```
